text: Taliaferro County is a county in the U.S. state of Georgia. As of the 2020 census, 1,559 people lived there. The county seat is Crawfordville. ==References== Category:1820s establishments in Georgia (U.S. state) Category:1825 establishments in the United States Category:Georgia (U.S. state) counties
